meta {
  name: Update Assignment Weights
  type: http
  seq: 11
}

put {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/users/assignment-weights
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Cookie: auth_token={{authToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "weights": [
      { "user_id": "{{userId}}", "weight": 50 },
      { "user_id": "{{secondUserId}}", "weight": 50 }
    ]
  }
}

docs {
  Sets the % share of new leads each user should auto-receive within the
  caller's org. Requires org_admin rank or above.

  Rules enforced server-side:
  - Every user_id must already be an active, in-range-rank member of
    iam.user_org_mapping for this org (same eligibility resolveAutoAssignedUser
    uses) — otherwise the request is rejected with 400.
  - The weights must sum to exactly 100, OR all be 0 (which disables
    auto-assignment for the org — new leads stay unassigned, same as today).
  - Changes are NOT retroactive — only future unassigned leads (Meta sync,
    manual lead creation without an explicit assigned_user_id) are affected.

  Example: one user at 100 and another at 0 sends every new lead to the
  first user. Two users at 50/50 split evenly; on an odd lead count the
  extra lead goes to whichever user currently has the larger workload
  deficit (random tiebreak if exactly equal).
}
